Parliament, Tuesday, 8 May 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will be briefed by National Treasury on the consolidated report on deviations and expansions for national departments and entities for the first quarter of 2018. Details of the briefing: Date: Wednesday, 9 May 2018
	Time: 09:30
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8062
